**The Science of Aesthetics: Why UI/UX is More Than Pretty Colors.**

For the frontend of Silo I did not want to build another to-do list. I wanted to build a workspace that felt calm and structured. I also wanted it to be "unignorable " a word I learned during my internship. 🌲

Here is how I approached the UI for this project:

**The Tech Stack:**

- React

- Vite

- TypeScript

- Tailwind CSS

Why Silo feels different:

- Bento Grid Layout: I organized the dashboard into easy-to-use tiles. This "Bento" approach makes complex data easy to understand at a glance.

- Industrial Zen Aesthetic: I chose a Forest Green and Mint color palette. It is easy on the eyes for work sessions.

- Type-Safe Development: I used TypeScript because it helps catch bugs during development.

- Micro-interactions: Every interaction is designed to provide feedback to the user.

**The Lesson:** Design is not just about how it looks; it is, about how it helps the user be productive. A designed tool reduces stress and keeps you focused.

